cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.DC

The paper deals with safety-critical distributed cyber-physical systems, which involve the integration of computation, communication, and physical processes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis, design, and control of complex systems. The paper also focuses on the coordination and communication between multiple agents, which suggests the category cs.RO (Robotics and Automation). The use of intelligent algorithms and the analysis of safety properties suggest the categories cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a decentralized approach for safety verification, which involves the exchange of information between agents, suggesting the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
